Historically, $DOGE  has spent long periods grinding sideways after major pullbacks - only to break out violently once conditions align. In previous cycles, similar consolidation phases ended with outsized upside moves once momentum flipped.  That said, not everyone is leaning bullish. From a risk perspective, DOGE is still leaning heavily on its long-term 350-day moving average, a level that has defined prior bear market floors.
